law.text:
A court-designated worker shall not:
Issue arrest or search warrants;
Supervise a child following his adjudication when the child is committed to the cabinet or placed on probation under the supervision of the cabinet or any other agency or individual;
Perform any clerical work not directly related to required juvenile activities;
Investigate child abuse, neglect, or dependency allegations but shall refer such actions to the cabinet; or
Dispose of complaints, except as authorized by KRS 605.030 or 635.010.
